Class SocialNetworkGraph

java.lang.Object
ie.ucd.csnl.comp47500.implementation.GraphImpl<UserProfile>
ie.ucd.csnl.comp47500.implementation.SocialNetworkGraph
All Implemented Interfaces:
Graph<UserProfile>
public class SocialNetworkGraph extends GraphImpl<UserProfile>
Represents a social network graph specifically tailored for analyzing user interactions. This class extends GraphImpl to handle vertices specifically designed as UserProfile, which include user profiles and their interactions.

  • Method Details

    • calculateInfluenceScores

      public void calculateInfluenceScores()
      Calculates the influence scores for all users in the graph. The score is determined by the strength of the interactions each user has in the graph. The strength of each interaction is added up to form the total influence score of a user. (like, comment, share, follow) to calculate the total influence score for each user. Recipient will get the score.

    • findKeyInfluencers

      public List<UserProfile> findKeyInfluencers(int topN)
      Identifies the top N influencers in the graph based on their influence scores. Influencers are sorted by their scores in descending order.
      Parameters:
      topN - The number of top influencers to return.
      Returns:
      A list of the top N influencers as UserProfile objects.

      Parameters:

      to - The ending vertex of the interaction.
      type - The type of social interaction.
      bidirectional - Indicates whether the edge should be bidirectional.
